th the initial stages of an infinitesimal theory for algebraic cycles. The book aims in part to understand the geometric basis and the limitations of Spencer Bloch's beautiful formula for the tangent space to Chow groups. Bloch's formula is motivated by algebraic K-theory and involves differentials over Q. The theory developed here is characterized by the appearance of arithmetic considerations even in the local infinitesimal theory of algebraic cycles. The map from the tangent space to the Hilbert scheme to the tangent space to algebraic cycles passes through a variant of an interesting construction in commutative algebra due to Angéniol and Lejeune-Jalabert. The link between the theory given here and Bloch's formula arises from an interpretation of the Cousin flasque resolution of differentials over Q as the tangent sequence to the Gersten resolution in algebraic K-theory. The case of 0-cycles on a surface is used for illustrative purposes to avoid undue technical complications.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aMATHEMATICS / Algebra / Abstract.2bisacsh  aAddition.  aAlgebraic K-theory.  aAlgebraic character.  aAlgebraic curve.  aAlgebraic cycle.  aAlgebraic function.  aAlgebraic geometry.  aAlgebraic number.  aAlgebraic surface.  aAlgebraic variety.  aAnalytic function.  aApproximation.  aArithmetic.  aChow group.  aCodimension.  aCoefficient.  aCoherent sheaf cohomology.  aCoherent sheaf.  aCohomology.  aCokernel.  aCombination.  aCompass-and-straightedge construction.  aComplex geometry.  aComplex number.  aComputable function.  aConjecture.  aCoordinate system.  aCoprime integers.  aCorollary.  aCotangent bundle.  aDiagram (category theory).  aDifferential equation.  aDifferential form.  aDifferential geometry of surfaces.  aDimension (vector spa